Palpal femur extremely bulky and modified with two ventral extensions. Distal femur extension (actually located centrally) quite pointed, with its tip slightly shifted distally (
Fig. 7d
). Proximal femur extension broader, also pointed and more strongly sclerotised. Palpal patella also very bulky. Palpal tibia distinctly short and with ventral process. The latter with long bristles directed retrolaterally (
Fig. 7b
).

Variation of copulatory organs. In males the two apophyses proximal to E may vary in length ( Figs 7a–c , 8a–c ). In females the size of anterior width of MS may differ ( Figs 7f ,
8g –h
). In some specimens an additional SH arises at base of SH-stalk ( Figs 7e , 8f ). Mostly this applies to only one vulva-half. Lengths of SH-stalks may differ slightly ( Figs 7e , 8d ).
